<item>
 <title>Junik</title>
 <link>http://jazz.to/artist/junik</link>
 <description>&lt;div class=&quot;field field-name-field-web field-type-link-field field-label-inline clearfix field-wrapper&quot;&gt;&lt;div  class=&quot;field-label&quot;&gt;website:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;http://giampaoloscatozza.com&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;http://giampaoloscatozza.com&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;body field&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;The new Album Karma takes everything I like in Junik - free improvisation, club-electronic sounds with strong melodies and combines with a Canadian, local groove. Giampaolo Scatozza teamed up with Richard Underhill, Steve Pelletier and Michael Occhipinti who are good friends and great musicians and he felt they would understand and express Junik’s music.&lt;/p&gt;
